{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1772200332,"nonce":"flqsBKzYuSdUSBySJTkZ+sYFGP0=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87s0Ef4","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/302#issuecomment-3973072888"},"message":"## Review\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Yes — the issue identifies three concrete deliverables: (1) add lifecycle labels to two skills, (2) create a centralized skills index, and (3) document the full lifecycle sequence. This is completable in a single PR.\n\n**Right repo?** Yes — this is workspace infrastructure documentation. The skills live in `.claude/skills/` in the workspace repo.\n\n**Dependencies**: None blocking. The skill collection (#282) is fully merged, so all skills to document already exist.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Only what's needed | **Watch** | The scope is reasonable, but the new document should be lean — a single table or list, not a lengthy guide. The lifecycle is a ~6-step sequence; resist expanding it into a multi-page document. |\n| A change includes its consequences | **OK** | The issue already identifies the specific files that need lifecycle labels added. |\n| Capture decisions, not just implementations | **OK** | This is literally capturing a design decision (the skill lifecycle) that currently exists only in an issue comment. Good. |\n| Improve incrementally | **OK** | Small, focused documentation addition. |\n| Primary framework first, portability where free | **Watch** | The skills are Claude Code-specific (`.claude/skills/`). A centralized doc could be placed in `.agent/knowledge/` if it describes the workflow generically (brainstorm → triage → plan → implement → review), or in `.claude/` if it's specifically about Claude Code skills. The issue doesn't specify — worth deciding during implementation. |\n\n### ADR Applicability\n\n| ADR | Triggered | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0006 — Shared AGENTS.md | **Maybe** | If the skill lifecycle is relevant to all agent frameworks (the workflow pattern is generic), it could be referenced from `AGENTS.md`. If it's Claude Code-specific, it belongs under `.claude/`. |\n\n### Consequences\n\nPer the consequences map:\n\n- Adding a new document should be referenced from the framework adapter (`CLAUDE.md`) — the issue doesn't mention this but it should be in scope.\n- If lifecycle labels are added to `review-issue/SKILL.md` and `review-pr/SKILL.md`, no downstream consequences beyond the skills themselves.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Keep the centralized document minimal** — a table mapping skill → lifecycle position → one-line purpose is sufficient. Avoid duplicating content from individual SKILL.md files.\n2. **Decide placement early**: `.agent/knowledge/skill_lifecycle.md` (generic workflow) vs `.claude/skills/README.md` (Claude Code-specific index). Given that the skills are currently Claude Code-only, `.claude/skills/README.md` seems natural, with a reference from `CLAUDE.md`.\n3. **Include the `make_*` skills in the index** — the issue focuses on governance skills but there are ~20 `make_*` skills too. The index should at least mention them as a category, or it will feel incomplete.\n4. **Consider whether `audit-workspace` and `audit-project` belong in the lifecycle** — the issue's sequence from #282 is `brainstorm → review-issue → plan-task → implement → review-pr → audit-project`, but `audit-workspace` and `gather-project-knowledge` are periodic/on-demand, not per-issue. The document should distinguish lifecycle skills from utility skills.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772200892,"nonce":"p+KH2vtypIT5RTaguMaobUhAbwU=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87s0Pip","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/302#issuecomment-3973118121"},"message":"See #305 which will inform other frameworks about the skills, so placement can be for a generic workflow.","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772203804,"nonce":"MPqd5knoLjSnAUt0H9WwQBmnqrE=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87uTYFizwAAAAVjJ2VH"},"status":2}]}